text: There are certain dishes I love here and others not so much.  Didn't like the waffles at all.  However, they have great Asian food (soup and noodles) and club sandwhiches.  My dad likes the fried shrimp.  He also recommends the omelets. French fries are good but extra greasy.I like the atmosphere here because it's slow and casual.  Late night dining at snaps is great!  Service can be very yayyy slow though...
Food was decent at one time, now food and services are poor and they don't care.  Ignore complaints.

We come here for mid-night snacks (yep! we eat a lot!)
I must say their Prime Rib for $5.99-7.99 is really good.

Food is pretty good here including the chinese food.  I'm giving it 2 stars because when I ate there a few weeks ago with my wife & child we dined in.  While we were still eating I ordered some food to go for my kids at home & then when we got the bill we were charged $1.20 for a "to go" fee.  Being in the restaurant business I understand about a to go fee but only if you were to walk up to the counter or call in a to go order.  We were diners still dining in your establishment & we still got this "to go" charge.  I complained to the cashier & she recommended that I fill out this card that she handed to me & yes a female manager called me back but told me what I already got charged for.  There are so many other places in the area that you can get food to go without being hit for a to go fee & that is what I will do next time.  I mean come on, you rely on locals for business then treat them like that.  I really like the food here but will take my business to Sam's Town, Boulder Station, or Arizona Charlies instead.  Please Boyd Gaming take over already & turn that place around.

Worst service of any restaurant.  asked for two cups of coffee , brought one cup, said we ordered two, never came back with the other cup.  ordered three dinners, offered soup or salad to only one of us.  Mentioned we did not give our soup or salad order, waitress just walked away.  Did not bring any cranberry sauce with turkey dinner,  asked for some,  reply we are OUT.

I've been here several times and overall the food is very good.

Sandwiches and burgers in the $7-8 dollar range are above average. I recommend the triple decker reuben sandwich- lots of good quality corned beef- ask them for the dressing on the side though as they tend to drown it. Burgers are good- recommend the patty melt. Downside is the fries are sub par.

I've also tried a couple of their Chinese dinners and they aren't too good IMO- pass on those.

Service is typical Vegas- hit or miss and usually at a snails pace.

The restaurant can get very crowded during peak meal times.

I don't know if it was my low, practically nonexistent  expectations of this restaurant, or my hunger but I was pleasantly surprised by the food here. It was solid coffee shop food. Not cheap though as I would expect from the East side Cannery,  I paid $8.99 for the Southwestern Chicken sandwich and fries.  I was torn between my normal coffee shop pick of eggs benedict or breakfast, as I pretty much know what to expect from coffee shop breakfast or the risky chicken sandwich pick - I took the risk.  I was expecting the chicken sandwich to be jerky dry as is my general experience with chicken sandwiches. The chicken was a little dry but by no means as dry as I thought it would be. The bacon the sandwich was not crispy, possibly the precooked microwavable kind, but it was edible. The portion size was decent and I left quite full for lunch.  The chipotle mayo was on the side which was great because then I could gauge how much mayo I put on the sandwich. I didn't try the pickle. You could choose between potato salad, coleslaw or french fries. I picked french fries they were frozen, not fresh, but at least they were hot when they came out.  I will say that I used a little trick I learned from a friend and ordered the fries without the salt to guarantee that they would have to make them/fry them upon order and I wouldn't get fries that had been sitting around. I don't always do this but based on the other yelp reviews complaining of cold fries I felt this was an strategy that needed to be implemented here. Service was extremely slow and lunch took well over an hour, but our server was friendly at least. 

So I was also debating between "meh" two stars and A-OK three stars, but with the friendly service I picked three - yes there are better coffee shops out there so I would probably give them 2 1/2 but as it stands and we can't do 1/2 stars I will go with A-OK.  I don't anticipate ever going back as this really wasn't my cup of tea and it is not conveniently located for me but if you are there already it is solid coffee shop fare.

I have eaten here four times and the food is inexpensive but below average.  Get in the car and go down the street to Sam's Town where they have more and better dining choices.  Even TGIFriday's is much better than this.

This rates in the top three worst meals I've ever had.  We had the special which was sliced beef on a sub style bun with fries and coleslaw.

Meat was thin, tough and tasteless, bun was dry, fries cold, and coleslaw was warm and tasted rancid.  

We had a nice server but she didn't come back to check on us (no doubt she new how bad the food was), she showed up after we stacked up the plates and said we have to order a drink with the special and she didn't know that.  We ordered a drink which took a long time to arrive, along with our bill.

When paying, we were asked how it was and I said pretty much inedible.  She said we should have told our server and that was the end of that.

Stupidly, we went back in the morning because you get a free breakfast and we thought how can they screw up eggs and toast!  Hashbrowns were obviously defrosted when they cooked them and became a mash, toast was so cold there was no way to butter it.  Coffee was supposed to be Starbucks but they must water it down a lot.

Snaps is great for cheap eats and good food. A few years back Snaps was terrible, food and service. They have made changes for the better. Wine by the bottle is 8 bucks !!! Music to my ears!!! Try the salmon dinner, blackened or any of their sandwiches! The Eastside club is the bomb!!

The food is actually pretty good.  Don't go there expecting 5 diamond cuisine....but if you're in the mood a burger or other American type sandwich, this is your place. The prices are really reasonable and the staff is super helpful and attentive.  I have yet to have had a meal I didn't enjoy at Snaps.
Gross gross made me and my daughter throw up! Go to the deli. If there closed denny's is across the street.  I hate denny's but it's still 100 times better.

The general tso's chicken is the best I've had anywhere. Pricing is extremely reasonable and the staff were very friendly. East side Cannery hotel is the best, we absolutely love staying here, our new "go-to" when visiting Vegas.

Nice place and service was better than expected. I however ordered a steak that came up undercooked. I asked the server to cook it a bit more. It took 20 more minutes to get my meal back. Everything else was fine. Alma was my server and I have to say she was pleasant and prompt and her help Romana was on the top of her game. I would recommend this place despite a little hiccup with the kitchen.

Omygosh....yummy all around. Cleanlines. Reasonable price. Great staff. Who would think that one can find Chinese food in a restaurant located in the middle of a casino. Thank you to Chef Steve and his excellent wait staff.

Delicious food! The steak is awesome and the frisco burger was to die for. Even the chicken parmesan was delicious! The only downside were the mashed potatoes and gravy which tasted fake. All in all, a wonderful meal! Five stars!

It's like Denny's but a tiny bit better.

I dunno what's up with the service in this casino, but it was all the same. Not super friendly and not very prompt. The food was a little better than what you would find at your local Denny's and pricing is decent. If you want a decently quick breakfast and are staying in the hotel, it's worth a try. 

I will say that I wouldn't take the effort to cross the street to eat here, or if the wait was longer than like 5 minutes.
Ordered the dues dues that comes along with hashbrowns French toast eggs and bacon or sausage. As you see I got extra bacon and my bill was $12.48
Open face turkey sandwich is great......

Ate here one late night food was decent from what i can remember only thing is dennys is next door damn near and being that Snaps is n a casino it can get smokey . Sorry but not being a cigarette person definitely dont like the smell while trying to enjoy a meal . they were priced decently so cant complain on that note i feel like i got my $s worth . But me personally not into inhaling someone elses nicotin so i prolly wouldnt venture back

OK here's the deal. I went the first time and didn't like it at all. Since it is close to the house, we tried it one more time... well what a difference! We have been back about 10 times in the last year since. Here is the scoop... Do NOT have any fried food here. They are the worst at frying anything. It is always all breading, super greasy, and gross. stay away from it!
Now here is what you SHOULD do... ALWAYS ask for Richard's area. He is super fast, very polite waiter. The best there. I would not want to eat there with anyone else as my server. The eastside cannery club is very good. The steak and eggs are fantastic. It is a nice steak, tender and juicy (if you get it Med rare like I do). The omelets and burgers are always good too. Also the cashew chicken. Their Chinese is surprisingly good.
So there you go!

We had breakfast here and the food was good. Our waitress Tenikia was cool. She got our food to us fast and made sure we had all that we needed. The orange juice tasted a little funny. 
The food was a good portion. Did not have any issues. The place could use some new updates on the decors.  The price was reasonable. It all and all was an ok place to eat.
Ate here for breakfast. The food was good (I had the eggs Benedict with hash browns) the place was clean and the staff was helpful, friendly and patient.

This place has me coming back for the sentimental reasons (Dad's favorite place), very close to home, and the selected few items..

I think I've tried almost everything on the menu -- from breakfast : skillets, biscuits with gravy, pancakes, waffles, the usual bacon, eggs, omelettes, to lunch : chicken wings/fingers with fries, burgers, sandwiches, soups, salads, and dinner : infamous fried chicken with mash & veggies, prime rib, New York steak, spaghetti and meatballs, fettuccine, salmon, and their Chinese food.

A well rounded menu if you ask me. I guess something for anyone to enjoy.

Few of my favorites..
*Fried Chicken - always told it's made to order, can take 20-30 mins to make, comes with side of potatoes and veggies. I've asked to change to veggie to broccoli and broccoli is a $1 more.. Why? Because it's the only other veggie they have? 
Chicken is nonetheless very crispy on the outside and really moist and juicy on the inside.
*Pork Fried Rice - the usual BBQ pork, peas and carrots type of fried rice, really simple yet done right!
*Hong Kong Style Pan Fried Noodles - crispy noodles topped with gravy, carrots, bokchoy, baby corn, mushrooms, and beef, I love ANY pan fried noodles!
*Chicken Potstickers - my son's favorite, pan fried and filled with lots of chicken, I believe it's 6 in an order.
*Wor Wonton Soup - love the broth, wontons are filled with lots of meat, and veggies are always cooked right.
*Breakfast Skillet - big portion for one order, your choice of meat, veggies, cheese, all scrambled with eggs on a bed of potatoes.

I must add they're 30% inconsistent.. I've gone here and have had some of the items a bit on the saltier side or not cooked right at all.
Service is a hit and miss too. Otherwise they're all still friendly.

Really can't go wrong especially if you're in the area or in the Eastside Cannery gambling because we know how long (or short) that could take and can leave you being hungry after winning (or losing)!

I ate here after arriving at the Eastside Cannery after hours of traveling, and I was super impressed by the food and prices. I ordered the Sunrise breakfast; not only was my meal delicious but it was super cheap: less than $10! The waiters were very friendly and on top of it as well. I decided to eat here again for lunch and was delighted once again. I simply ordered grilled cheese with fries; you can pick your bread and cheese which I really like. It's the little things folks! Even if you're not staying here, the food is so cheap, how can you pass it up?!?!?

Shame on me, I guess, for ordering Chinese food at a non-Chinese location.

I wasn't really impressed with the Hong Kong noodles that I received.  The vegetable choice was a bit strange and everything was drowned in a thick gravy.  The noodles themselves were really soggy and not really crispy as I've typically found at Chinese restaurants.

Maybe I'll have to come back and try some of the non-Chinese food.

We stay at Eastside Cannery almost everytime we go to Vegas. Snaps is a great cafe, the servers are friendly, the food is good, glasses refilled without having to beg.

The prices are reasonable. From breakfast to the Asian dishes each has been delicious.

The biscuits and gravy are fantastic.

Look forward to eating there next time.

This is a nasty excuse for a restaurant. Last night, I got food poisoining and was dumping and vomiting at the same time. It was the chicken philly - how do I know - because I threw the whole damn sandwich up in the shower. Hell will be raised and unless you want to suffer the same fate, stay away from this lowlife part of town and disgusting excuse for a restaurant.
Snaps. Is good food and budget friendly.  Waiters are friendly and helpful.  Always ready to make sure everything is ok.

So much food for so little money! 

Snaps is a great dining option if you don't want fine dining or a buffet.

They have great specials and so many options. From Asian Specialties and all day breakfast favorites such as steak and eggs or French toast, you really can't go wrong by choosing to eat here.

If you play in the casino and have a players card, be sure to ask for a comp from the hosts.

I enjoy the steak and eggs as well as the shrimp cocktail. Both are inexpensive and will keep you full for the daily grind on the casino floor.

There's never too long if wait and service is quick.

If you're pressed for time, you can also place your order To Go!

Only a few steps from the hotel lobby and casino, you'll never go hungry.

I've been here a few times and never left upset.

Thanks Snaps and crew for keeping me and my friends full without breaking the bank! 

Be back soon!

They serve authentic Chinese food like the Shrimp fried rice, hongkong style chow mein, beef broccoli etc etc. 
However they need to add more selections

We eat here two times a week or more.Today we had a Denver omelette and egg white omelette w/ spinach.Food was great,service too.Brenda is usually our server,she always sees to it that our orders are just so.Some of our favorite menu items are:The classic club,signature french toast that's dipped in frosted flakes,Wor bar soup,Kung Pao shrimp,shrimp fried rice,Asian salmon salad.Seniors 55+ get 50% off your check Sun and Mon.when signed up for the Can Club.Cant beat it.

Nothing much to say about this restaurant. Its next to the a slot machines, it's cheap but the food is not particularly good.

It's OK if you're really hungry!

Management needs to learn how to effectively utilize their team. The bussers need more responsibility. They need to be doing more than just filling drinks and cleaning tables. The busser was filling our drinks to the point that it was annoying they didn't even need to be filled. But the opposite with the server, she was so overwhelmed we barely saw her. While she ran around like a chicken with her head cut off the busser repeatedly wipe down the same clean table over and straightened placemats on the same table. Restaurant 101, allow your busser to have more tasks to lighten the load of the server which is going to result in a happier customers who come back. If I wasn't a server and able to see what is happening I may not come back. 

Additionally when we were sat it was an extremely long time before we saw a server and when we asked the busser about the server she stated she's in the back. And just continued filling drinks never attempted to go find the server. Obviously the server is busy and can't drop everything right that second but any restaurant I've ever worked in over the course of the 20 something years that I worked in restaurants if you see (which I'm sure she did) a table that is sitting there for a ridiculous amount of time and they ask for a server, then you need to go get a manager and the manager needs to take the order. To try to salvage the situation. All of this is a reflection of management and not the team.

Lastly the fruit plate says it comes with a muffin but the muffin didn't come on my plate when I asked for it I got a minuscule itty-bitty tiny muffin that smelled like a foot. When I started to unwrap them up and I smelled is rancid terrible smell and I put it closer to my nose and almost puked. The fruit plate is almost $10 if you can't provide a decent muffin then take the muffin out of the description. When I went for breakfast I experienced very good service. Biscuits and gravy are disgusting. All the other reviews on here that they are really good blows my mind, if you want really good biscuits and gravy consistently go to the skyline. I've lived in this town for 20 something years and still haven't found anybody that can compare to them. The biscuits and gravy here need some kind of salt and pepper maybe some bacon grease or sausage grease, it's basically cream with disgusting pieces of huge chunks of meat. You need to salt the fries when they come out of the fryer. Also I cannot stand when restaurants deep-fry bacon. It's lazy and it ruins the bacon. 

When this place first open many years ago I tried the café and had a terrible experience but wanted to try again, it's better but lots of room for improvement.

I will never eat there again waitress took15 minutes for drink order brought it back quick wrong waited there over 20 minutes no one came back threw a 5 on the table for the coffee we got and left the hostess chased us down saying we didn't pay for the coffee I told her the 5 was on the table she said well that would be for the server I just looked at her and said if I walk back there better be a manager I can speak to she said never mind and walked away they suck

The only good thing about here is that the servers were nice, attentive, and friendly, other than that, the proportions of food compared to the price is not worth it. Ordered a $10 pork chop, and the size of the meat is only half the size of what Tuscany Casino offers(which is only $9 dollars). Their fried rice was good, but their other Asian entree are full of batter, that when I ordered Salt & Pepper Sea Bass, I can barely taste fish. I would only go back here for the fried rice.

The clam chowder soup was broken and that is the worst when you like New England clam chowder. I was very disappointed the server is OK not over the top or anything. Vanilla milkshake was very good. Ordered mild chicken wings and they came out extra hot.

I had a coupon for the T-bone deal at Snap's. I took my wife to dinner tonight. I had the steak dinner and she had ordered the fish and chips.  We had never had a problem there until tonight. Why the four star rating?  Here is why... (Stations Casino could take notes here, btw):  our waitress was pleasant, but that was it.  Her name was Diane.  She put the order for my steak in as extra extra well done.  Really?  I ordered it medium well.  I never got my butter for the veggies. My wife's meal was great, except no tarter sauce for her fish.  We never got the bill, or even seen Diane again.  I explained to the cashier that the waitress sucked ass, as did my meal, and i never got the check.  This is where the manager at the Grand Cafe at Sunset Station could learn something.  The other cashier, Victoria stepped in.  She listened to our complaint (and didn't laugh at me like the bitch at the Grand Cafe at Sunset Station did).  She contacted the manager, Sammy, whom was there in less than a minute.  She listened to us, looked at the order, and apologized to us both.  She gave me the coupon back, said lets try this another time, and voided the entire bill.  THIS is why four stars.  These two stepped up to do their best to make things right.  I had to remove one for the waitress.  Again, I have never had a problem at Snap's, I will dine there again, and very much thank Victoria and Sammy for a job well done. I have never stepped into a Stations Casino since they pulled what they did six months ago. But I will continue to enjoy the fine dinning at Snap's and their buffet is pretty good also.

Went to this place inside the Eastside Cannery two days in a row to meet with family while on vacation!  I was real pleased to see how the staff greets the locals, knowing them by name and treating them like family. Says alot about a place. Our server both days, Lee was a doll. She was attentive and handled out table of  six the first day and all ten the next without breaking a sweat. She keeps up with the wize alecs too! A nice place with good food. The price is right and the pictures all over the place are cute too! Clean and neat I would go again.

I would rate Snaps at about 3.5. Considering the location the service and food wasn't too bad. The nachos are the best. They are served with guacamole, sour cream, and salsa all in side cups so its not so messy. The prices are really affordable.

Whoa!  Something has changed @ Snaps and it's the quality of the food!

On our last visit a year or so ago, I really thought that we were in a low quality Denny's.  The food was bland and yucky.  Both our items seemed like they had just come out of the freezer bag and off the warming rack.

Then last night we took a chance and hit it up again and I am so glad to report that the food quality has gone way up from our last experience.

I wanted prime rib and they were running a $9.99 special.  I wasn't sure what to expect, but I thought I'd take the risk and I am glad I did.  The prime rib was amazingly good.  Juicy, tender and very flavor-able.  For a minute you could close your eyes and imagine yourself @ Lawry's!!! Well maybe not quite that, but very, very good.

My wife had the Chinese and it too was tasty and fresh.  

I hope they keep these improvements since it's a place that is close to home and I like to play the nickle video poker machines at the Eastside Cannery.

This is my boss's favorite spot to eat I think so I've been here a few times.  I haven't had a bad meal yet surprisingly.  Kinda surprised by the poor reviews.  The chinese food is good - I've only had the orange chicken but it was tasty.  Also the country club was really good with bacon and fresh avocado. I'd recommend this little spot and prices aren't really your typical outrageous casino prices either.

The food is good and the service is even better. Hell the price is reasonable. I find that service is always what I look at first. Snaps has an awesome staff and the servers are some of the best I have personally experienced in an off the strip restaurant.

Good job guys.
Middle of the road.   Had Chicken fried steak.   It was good, hash browns cooked last week, tough and cold. Eggs warm but dry.    Service good.
Love the breakfast special, with Biscuits and Gravy. Delicious at a great price. It's a Saturday morning thing.....

Came here to eat since I was staying in the hotel. Seems like they do not know their crowds. Big parties are here but it seems like they did not have Enoch staff for a Sunday morning.  They should know what to expect when the hotel is nearly booked up.  Took them 15 to take my order for a simple bacon and eggs and nearly 20 minutes to get the food.  When it came is was really nothing special, toast was cold eggs were warm not even hot.  I would have sent it back but I did not want to wait another 10-15 minutes for them to bring it back.  Go to Denny's across the street anything is better than this.

We come here specifically for the Wonton Soup. It's delicious. Filled with really flavorful  tender wontons that hold up great in the piping hot delicious broth. The bowl  is loaded  with fresh vegetables and of strips of tender pork. The vegetables in the soup are bok choy, carrots, water chestnuts, pea pods, broccoli, scallions all fresh. We always get a side of  egg rolls with HOT MUSTARD (wow it is so hot and delicious). If you love wonton soup you will love this bowl and it's very reasonably priced.

I've been here twice before.  The first time when it opened back in 2008.  I came today because it was my fathers birthday and decided to buy him lunch.  This was this place he requested to go to. We started off with wings and fries.  We ordered mild wings and the were some barn burners.  Kinda hot for mild but that's ok.  The fried were those thick fries like some old man fingers but delicious.  We both got New York strips and it came with a baked potato.  A side of vegetables came with the plate.  I ordered my steak rare and it was actually rare but had a burnt taste on the outside.  All in all it was a good meal and I enjoyed taking pops out for his birthday.  The End

While driving around on Christmas Eve looking at Christmas lights we passed by the Eastside Cannery and decided to see what they had to eat.

After looking at the menu at Snaps we knew this would be the place to try something new. It is decorated with a 1960's feel. 

The hostess greeted us and seated us right away. It was just after 8 pm and they were pretty busy. I was at least given a menu to look over but it took 10 minutes for someone to acknowledge us and get our drink order. It was frustrating but since it was Christmas Eve and they did appear busy I figured it might not always be like that.

We started off with "Idaho Potato Wedges" that only cost $3.99. It had Shredded Cheddar, Sour Cream, Chopped Bacon, and Green Onions on the wedges. You will get way more then you thought for the price and they taste great.

Since it was so cold outside I thought the "Homemade French Onion Soup" sounded comforting. It was! The portion was perfect and the Swiss Cheese was just bubbling over the top. Under the cheese a very thick bread that soaked up and held up nice considering all of the yummy cheese on top of it. The broth had a very deep flavor and the onions were so flavorful. It only cost $4.50!!!

My man had what they call a "Monster Burger". It has Fried Egg, Onion Rings, Cheddar Cheese and Pastrami. He had them leave the egg off. He said the burger could have been seasoned better but the pastrami was very good. 

The inside was clean and the staff friendly.

You can choose booth or table. They have some bigger tables for larger parties. 

They serve beer and wine. There is a bar and they have plenty of tvs to watch sports on.

If you are hankering for some Chinese food they have a separate Chinese menu!

At one end of the bar you will notice the take out sign for all to go/pick up orders.

Check the website for the Cannery to see the deals/promotions they have going on in Snaps. They currently have a few very good meal specials. 

I'm so glad we tried Snaps! We will for sure be back!

Ellie was our waitress this morning and she was absolutely amazing! My brother has severe epilepsy and is on a medical diet and she went above and beyond to help us out and was so sweet about it! She was funny and also timely. She made the expierience at this restaurant a great one! The food wasn't too bad either :).

Food's not bad here, better than a so so diner I'd say.

What can't be beat are their 24/7 specials like prime rib dinner for $7.99 or filet mignon - surf and turf for $9.99.  They also have grave yard specials like two eggs, hash brown and bacon w/toast for $1.99 or  pancakes w/bacon or sausage for $1.99.

I had the prime rib dinner that came w/soup or salad, dinner rolls, baked or mashed potato and vegetables.  Not a bad deal at all.  The rolls were actually really yummy, but they had the super market baked taste.  I chose soup - chicken noodle that came in a cup the size of a large tea cup.  The salad was standard - ice berg lettuce.  My steak was a really good size.  Not the best prime rib of course, a little over done.. not cooked too properly, but still good.  Came w/tons of butter, au jus sauce and horse radish.  Can't beat that!

The breakfast special was good too, I had the pancakes w/sausage and the pancakes were enormous and fluffy!

The menu items are standard american fare but they also had an entire page of asian food! I could only wonder how they tasted.

What I like are also the small things they include, like the fries w/your burger comes in a small little deep fryer net, cute.
Friendly staff, large portions, and delicious food! Great prices! Water is disgusting your better off drinking sink water.

New Years Eve.....Lots of empty tables. ....super slow service.   20 minutes in line to get in.  Looks bad to wait when you see all these empty tables.  Guess half the wait staff called in sick?  Heaven help those that come later when it's probably gonna be busier.

I have ate hear twice, for both breakfast and dinner. The country fried steak is good, the biscuits and gravy are aslo quite nice. The service has always been very good as well. I really don't have anything bad to say about them. Much better than Denny's or I-hop and about the same price.

Food was alright, I got chicken wings they needed to be cooked a little more, well done steak was cooked but burned. Not bad but not good service was very plain. Not Sweet , talkative, friendly. Eh I enjoy upbeat servers I'm a good tipper as well but had to tip the women $3 because I was really disappointed with her service. Don't get me wrong she got orders correct but serving is putting in a show and it was plain

Javier host was very welcoming and professional. Seated right away. Esmi luv her. Gr8t friendly staff. Had a 1/4 Beef Hot dog w/ fresh relish and plump n crispy steak-like fries and a juicy fresh pickle wedge. Very Fresh!! Hit the spot! Service

I give 1 star only because I cannot give 0 stars.

Terrible service.
Terrible food.
Slowly, disaffected service.
Good was very decent! Richard was our server and he's just awesome. We ordered generals tsaos chicken and Kung pao shrimps and steak and eggs, everything tastes good and totaled 30$.

After a long day of showing the city to my sweetheart we came back to the hotel starving. We went into Snaps for a quick snack before bed and they didn't disappoint. OMG a short stack for $1.99 you can't beat late night munchie food like pancakes and at this price so cool. My girl got Parmesan Onion Rings they were huge and very good.

Can't beat the comfort food and the prices!
French dip was very tasty- good coleslaw also. Hubby had fried chicken & he said one of the best he's had. Tasty & juicy!

Snaps was fine for breakfast.  I have been here two or three times for dinner, but I didn't review at that time.

Today, I had the Build Your Own omelet with spinach, mushrooms, and jack cheese.  Tomato slices instead of potatoes and rye toast.  Price was $5.99.  

Service was very good.  The toast wasn't buttered much in the kitchen and she brought extra butter quickly.

I like this coffee shop.

Didn't know what to expect since I've never even heard of the Cannery until a couple hours ago. At 3am, it was expected that this place would be deserted. Efficient service, not super but it sufficed. Considering there was only 2 or 3 other parties here before us, the food did take some time to arrive after we ordered. 

The bf ordered steak and eggs, I ordered the mushroom spinach omelette. Though it took a while, the food was really good!! Huge portion sizes and yummy taste. I would say the food made up for the slow food time.

I'd come back again!!

Pretty good place to eat. The times I've been have been good customer service and speedy service. The line is usually not that long to get in and get seated. If you like breakfast it is served 24hrs here and it's always been good. The area is not so great around the Eastside Cannery is not the greatest but they do have parking security that will watch over your cars while parked.

Food: 4/5
Service: 4/5
Cleanliness: 4/5
Decor & Style: 3/5

Snaps is your typical vegas buffet food gone restaurant style, and surprisingly, was pretty good! Egg rolls were good, hash browns were good, fries were good. For a random variety I enjoyed my meal! 
This place feels like a modern diner IMO. Probably won't be back here unless I get some coupons/free meals.

Stayed in the hotel for 10 days and went to snaps everyday. I have to say their food is amazing for the price. They have a variety if different things you can get so you will never get sick of having the same thing. I would recommend having the taco salad or any of the steaks and omelets.

Great service! Richard is by far the best server here, he is always friendly, helpful and quick to get you anything you need. The burgers, wings and chinese are all amazing every time. Definitely try it out!(: (don't drink the coffee thoughO_O)

BE AWARE THEY CHARGE FOR TAKING FOOD TO GO. I ordered a whole entree to go, and got a $1.20 "open togo charge" added to my bill. Other than that, decent food, prices are ok, around $10 a person for entrees, but breakfast is a pretty cheap option. Not sure it's served all day but it's around $5. .

I happened to be hungry on the East side so I headed into the Cannery after reading positive remarks about their Mexican restaurant. Sadly, Casa Cocina (doesn't that just mean 'house of kitchen'?) is only open for dinner so we went to Snaps, their diner. Well, as you may have guessed the meal was pretty dull, but the highlight was the chicken soup. It was made from scratch, had a lot of flavor, and was well-seasoned. Most suprisingly, the egg noodles (someone in the kitchen knows the right noodles to use for chicken soup) were perfectly cooked without an inkling of sogginess. Had I ordered a bowl rather than a cup and passed on the sorry excuse for parmesan onion rings and cafeteria side salad I would have been quite happy. Just a little FYI in case you find yourself in the East Side Cannery and need something snappy....

This coffee shop is offering two $1.99 breakfast breakfast specials and we tried both.  Ms. Westie chose the 2 eggs (easy over), toast, bacon and hash browns while I feasted on 2 pancakes and bacon.  Both were very well executed and service was attentive. ($6.29)

A few days later I requested a comp from the Slot Shift Supervisor and received one for  $25.  Ms. Westie and I each ordered OJ, an avocado omelet and bacon. The omelets were satisfactory, but nothing to write home about.  The bill was an amazing $22.78.

Snaps is the Casino Café at the Eastside Cannery. It's had a lot of issues in the past, mainly in the service category, but it seems to be turning around. Our last experience here went pretty well and the food was very good.

Their menu, for the most part, is pretty standard with a few exceptions. All the traditional American fair is here, along with a Chinese menu. I can't really recommend the Chinese dishes, I've ordered off that menu twice in the past and wasn't impressed either time.

My wife and I ordered the club sandwich and the fried chicken. They warn you when you order the fried chicken that it is made fresh to order and usually takes between 20 to 30 minutes to make. Trust me that the wait is worth it if you like fried chicken. It's really juicy and perfectly seasoned. As for the club sandwich, it was great, mainly due to the bread. It's served on parmesan toasted bread and filled with sliced turkey, avocado and bacon. The parmesan bread kicks it up a notch and just makes this club standout over a typical one.

Most of my experiences here up until this meal have been at the two or three star level, but the service was good and the food was above average enough to warrant a fourth star. I just hope that this wasn't an abnormality, as I am looking forward to going back here again, though it is very likely my wife and I will just order the same thing.

Still love the War Wonton. Have tried others in the Valley, keep coming back here. It's the ultimate comfort food. The potstickers are pretty good, too. I guess they have an Asian cook who'll really knows his stuff.

This Christmas morning breakfast was perfect except for one stupid thing.  Too much pepper in the biscuits and gravy; hey chef, we can always add more pepper.  Have to give them 5 stars anyway.  Nice place, reasonable prices, good specials, and my pancakes and sausage were perfect as was the scrambled eggs that my wife had (I tasted).  Biscuits and Gravy could have had 5 stars without the pepper.

After a long night of watching fights we were starving. We ate pho earlier in the day which Is why we stayed full for so long. We decided to go get some stuff at the market which made us hungrier! We were making our way back down Boulder highway and because it was so late there weren't many options, so we decided to give snaps a go! I've eaten here years ago and honestly don't remember the food or service. Since its a new year I'm working on making healthier choices overall unless it's a full blown cheat day. I decided on a Chinese chicken salad and my future husband decided on the pot roast since Chinese wasn't available anymore. Chinese is over at 10'pm and it was 11 pm. I honestly was skeptical about a Chinese chicken salad or anything on the menu to be honest because usually food at a cafe is a hit or miss. My salad was definitely a pleasant surprise and a big hit! It was so good I could eat that salad everyday for the rest of my life and be super satisfied. It had a large bed of Napa cabbage and sliced red bell pepper along with mandarin oranges, crispy chow mein noodles and cashews. The cashews really made the salad they were roasted and crispy. Omgeeeee so nomilicious! My guy enjoyed his pot roast as well. Service was good and they kept our water glasses topped off. The bus boy even chased me out of the restaurant when I forgot my phone inside! I was so thankful and impressed. I will definitely be back for some more of that salad. I can't say enough about how good it was.

Can we say unorganized ? We are standing in line waiting on a table there are lots of people behind us, the couple in front of us wants a booth, there are at least 10 tables empty but we have to wait till a booth gets cleaned before anyone can set down is that crazy or what? We wanted a table , not a booth. Unbelievable ! But our waitress, Brenda, was great once we did get seated.

What... The... Heck?!
My husband and I stopped here before bingo. We waited a few minutes at the hostess desk, made eye contact with a few employees and continued to wait. Finally, the cashier came out from behind her counter to seat us. Our drink order was taken about five minutes after we sat down. Then we waited... And waited. I counted the tables. There were 8. I counted the servers... 5. What is going on here?! FINALLY, our order was taken. 22 minutes later the server informed us our food was still cooking. We now had 7 minutes until bingo started and I was noticeably irritated. He asked us if we wanted it "to-go" and I told him I wasn't taking my fish into the bingo hall. About five minutes later we got our food. My husband's chicken fried steak was great. My green beans were a little in the cool side. My fish was raw. Not under cooked, not Luke warm... RAW. It was cold and slimy. I actually spit it out. He came back around and when I told him the piece of fish I bit into was raw, he said, "all of them? Do you want me to take that one and you can continue eating the other ones?" Wow... Just... I can't even. I ate the baked potato and pushed the plate away. He took the fish off the bill and I asked him to just take my card and charge us for the other meal so we could get out of there.
Needless to say, we missed our bingo session and left angry and hungry. I will never eat at the Cannery again. The buffet was awful too!

So the buffet closes at 8 and we decided oh well we're going to eat at Snaps. OMG great choice. The food was really good. I had the cashew chicken and the flavor was really amazing. We also got the sea bass and the Philly cheese steak. Everyone was very pleased with the food and the service and did I say the prices were reasonable. I'll definitely be back. Wait service great.

We came here on a Wednesday evening and ordered 
1. Fish feast, 9.99
2. General Tso chicken, 7.99 with 1.49 upgrade 
for $18.65 (Used a coupon that we got in the mail: Buy 1 entree get the 2nd one for $3)

- Wanted to get the Fried chicken meal for 9.99 first but the server said that it would take at least 30min to make! Such a long time. So ended up getting the fish feast. Good deal. Big portion. Reminded me of something a little bit better than Long John's Silver. 
- We were a little bit nervous ordering Chinese food in a restaurant called Snaps, but it turned out to be pretty good. Although very salty, but I think that's how most Americans prefer their Chinese food, drench was soy sauce. 
- Friendly service. Attentive. 
- Nice diner setting. 
- The upgrade didn't apply to the chicken. It was 7.99-4=$3, not (7.99+1.49)-X=$3. Lame
- I'd probably come back when they have another deal in the mail or possibly for the breakfast specials.

I have eaten at Snaps a ton of times since they opened up the Cannery.  Hell, I even liked the diner at the old Nevada Palace when it was here.  The Eastside Cannery is close to home and it's a well run casino that is welcoming and warm.  The employees are great all around the casino and the same could be said at Snaps.  

I try and have dinner with my folks once a week.  Usually on my night of carb-feasting.  But, last week I went to a couple of UYE's and didn't get a chance to.  So, I made sure I would hook up with them this weekend.  I'm not much of a food snob and I'll go anywhere that is decent.  So, Snaps, the diner at the Eastside Cannery, was the call.  I like diners, there is always something  for everyone.  The menu varies, breakfast any time of the day to a Chinese menu.  But, I knew that I wanted breakfast with extra hash-browns.  That is a great carbload for me.  So, here was our night:

Parking is always easy to find at the Eastside Cannery.  I don't mind a little walk but, they have a shuttle if you need it.  Nice touch.  Anyhow, I met my folks in front of the restaurant and we were immediately seated in the back near the kitchen.  Our drink orders were taken pretty quickly.  Our waitress, Ronnie, came to our table to see if we had any questions before we ordered.  But, since we have been here many times before we knew what we wanted.  Ronnie takes our order and our drinks came out as soon as she left.  

The place was quiet - except for a drawing going on in the main casino and a nasty hum coming from the sound system.  That kind of got on my nerves but whatever.  It was quiet because one, it's a Sunday night and two, we were there at 5:00 pm.  It's what you get when you eat with the retired.

Our meals come out and everything looked great.  The food was hot and our drinks were always being refilled.  As we were finishing our meals I realized that I didn't get my 2nd order of hash browns and Ronnie made sure to take it off of the bill.  She was apologetic but it happens and wasn't a big deal.  So, for dinner it was just around the $30 mark and we left satisfied.

"Eh" is the best comment I can make about this place.  The food was alright, the service was seriously lacking.  When you have to beg to have your order taken, beg to get a refill, and then you don't even pay your server, what is the point of having a waitress?
What a joke, ask for a booth and was told to go and wait, they had plenty of booths, that's the customer service the east side cannery

Visited after quite an absence. The service was just OK. The food was terrible ! I had the fish and chips for $9.95. I received 3 big pieces of what I thought was fish and fries. WRONG! Each piece of fish had a very small piece of fish and at least 10X as much thick soggy batter....terrible!
 The fries were soggy and greasy!  NEVER again!

We stay at this casino every year when traveling to Phoenix. The people are wonderful and the food is good. Service is usually very quick. On occasion it can be a bit slow, but only when extremely busy b

This restaurant is 24 hours the menu is very cost effective and their food was amazing to say the least! Our waitress was friendly and prompt with delivering our food. Next time we're in town we will definitely, return. No more restaurants on the strip for me!

We eat at Snap quite often as it in the coffee shop inside the cannery casino and that is one of our regular gambling haunts.
The guys always have the Asian plates that they serve for dinner.  Usually getting a couple and splitting them.
I go for the Giant CFS with mashed pot's or the club sandwich.  Also one of my fav's in the Nevada Chicken.

Went here last night, tried broccoli beef.very surprised lots of beef and great flavor.wife had fettucini, she said that was horrible.will return to try other Chinese dishes.son has Mongolian beef and that was good.

I wish I could give half stars... I'd go for 2 1/2. This place is mediocre. The staff do their job but don't do it very fast, the food is hot and looks good but the potatoes are stale. It could be a lot better but it could also be a lot worse.

My wife and I had dinner and could not finish it. Fish was terrible probably frozen and thawed just before serving. The same thing for the vegetables. I would suggest eating elsewhere.
The service was good and people were friendly.

Been here a few times when we did not hit the buffet at Cannery.

We have tried breakfast, soup's, dinners .Depending on the time of day we have always received our food pretty fast and have never had a problem.

I have tried a few of the Chinese dishes here and have liked what I ordered. I also have gotten the  Cobb Salad  for $8.99 which is not too bad and it comes with 
Turkey, bacon, avocado, tomatoes, bleu cheese, eggs and cucumbers... Its a good size and really enjoyable!

Over the years of course depending on the server you get you usually always get good service as well.

If you gamble at the cannery you may receive coupons in the mail to use. That has been awhile since I have received any, but they do it.

They are open 24 hours but we have gone where they closed down for cleaning. 

Check them out when your in Cannery. The food is not bad at all.

This is a great place for breakfast and our server Lee was the best. The ham and eggs is the best with a 16+ oz of ham.
The hotel is also nice.

I had never been here before, and since we were seeing a show at the Eastside Cannery later that night, it seemed like a good time to try Snaps.  I never got past the Chinese menu, and was generally pleased with what was served.  But there were a few dirty utensils that needed to be replaced, and bits of sticky rice were found in two empty soup bowls which were quickly removed for new ones.

Vegetable Egg Rolls were tasty dipped in a very good vibrant, light Sweet & Sour Sauce, and well-prepared pan-fried Potstickers tasted very good.  Wor Wonton Soup contained an ample amount of bok choy, broccoli, celery, carrots, peapods, bamboo shoots, shrimp, chicken, pork, and juicy pork-filled wontons.  Kung Pao Shrimp featured baby corn cobs, celery, carrots, peanuts, sweet Red Peppers, hot Red Chili Peppers, and of course shrimp in a very spicy sauce.  Diane pronounced her Fish n Chips as good but "really greasy."  Service was friendly, efficient, and ubiquitous.

XXX-1/2 stars overall on this one outing

Wow super good lunch Ellie she was good got my NY steak perfect "welldone" medium rare!!!!
Meaning job well done lol.
A good way to start the day

My Milkshake brings all the boys to the yard... 

Mmmmm yes they do make a great shake, the glass is rimmed with the most sweetest and thick caramel one could imagine. Really adds a nice taste blend with a vanilla shake when you scrape the sides of the glass with your spoon! Can you say "Mouth Orgasm"?

I used to dine here a lot with my boyfriend Chris as he lived around the corner from Snaps. We ate here several times a month for close to a year and a half so we have tried many meals here! We still talk about our old Snaps days, lolol. Yes, seriously the restaurant is called "Snaps".

Service is hit and miss, sometimes we are ignored and sometimes they are up my ass with servicing me. 

The food quality is good and so are the portions. 

I really like having breakfast here, I think that is really their specialty.
Can't go wrong with denver omelet, pancakes, french toast and their signature skillets. Make sure you are HUNGRY! 

I have also tried from the Chinese menu and they make a great sweet and sour shrimp. Huge shrimps, mmmmm. 

They have a great sourdough burger in which I believe they now call the "Frisco" burger. Mmmmm try it, you will see what I am excited about. I have to cut this burger down with a knife every time just to fit it all in my mouth to eat. Thick buttery fried sourdough bread, bacon, guacamole, double cheese, 1/4 Angus patty, lettuce, tomato, purple onion and fried onion strings. Mmmmmm is soooooo good! 

Prices are reasonable however are slowly increasing lately and the restaurant is very comfortable with booths and tables. 

Snaps is located inside of the Eastside Cannery.

Try it!
